Package drawmaze

Class Cell

java.lang.Object
drawmaze.Cell
public class Cell extends Object
The 'Cell' class contains the fields for each cell, and deals with the neighbouring cells for each cell. Code adapted from and inspired by YouTube creator, Codamy: Maze generation: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zsG2ceOlY6I&t=3s&ab_channel=Codamy Maze solve: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_KEzW50Nhyw&ab_channel=Codamy There have been considerable changes to their code to adapt with this assignment.

  • Method Details

    • addNeighbours

      public void addNeighbours(Cell[][] cells, int numRows, int numCols)
      The 'addNeighbours()' method identifies and adds the neighbouring cells to a given Cell object in the 2D Cell array. This method adds a cell to the left of the cell in question to the 'neighbouringCells' ArrayList of Cells if it is greater than 0 (i.e. is not a cell whose left wall is the left border), adds a cell below the cell in question if it less than the total number of columns in the maze (i.e. is not a cell whose bottom wall is the bottom border), adds a cell to the right of the cell in question if it is less than the total number of rows in the maze (i.e. is not a cell whose right wall is the right border), and adds a cell above the cell in question if it is greater than 0 (i.e. is not a cell whose top wall is the top border).
      Parameters:
      cells - the 2D Cell array from the 'GenerateMaze' class.
      numRows - the number of rows in the maze which is used in the method along with the number of columns to identify which Cell object in the Cells array.
      numCols - the number of columns in the maze which is used in the method along with the number of rows to identify which Cell object in the Cells array.

    • checkUnvisitedNeighbours

      public boolean checkUnvisitedNeighbours()
      The 'checkUnvisitedNeighbours()' method iterates through each neighbour Cell in the 'neighbouringCells' ArrayList, and if the cell has not been visited, return true (the current cell in the 'definePath()' method in the 'GenerateMaze' class has unvisited neighbours), else return false (the current cell has no unvisited neighbours, i.e. only neighbours which have already been visited).
      Returns:
      true if the current cell has unvisited neighbours, else return false if the current cell has only visited neighbours.

    • chooseNeighbour

      public Cell chooseNeighbour()
      The 'chooseNeighbour()' method randomly chooses a neighbouring cell of the current cell in 'definedPath()' in the 'GenerateMaze' class. If the random number generator picks a neighbour which has already been visited, a new number will be randomly generated, and this will repeat until a neighbour that has not been visited is chosen.
      Returns:
      the chosen neighbouring Cell which has not been visited yet.

    • addMazePathNeighbours

      public void addMazePathNeighbours(Cell[][] cells)
      The 'addMazePathNeighbours()' method adds a specific cell's neighbouring cell in the maze solution path. There neighbour cell is determined by which of the specific cell's wall has not been drawn, as only one will not have been drawn.
      Parameters:
      cells - the 2D Cell array used in the 'GenerateMaze' class.
